HOUSE BILL 492
D1 6lr2569
CF SB 544
By: Chair, Judiciary Committee (By Request – Maryland Judicial Conference)
Introduced and read first time: January 27, 2026
Assigned to: Judiciary
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 6, 2026
CHAPTER _____
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Courtroom Security – Minimum Adequate Security Standard
3 FOR the purpose of establishing minimum adequate security standards for courtroom
4 security at all courthouse facilities; and generally relating to courtroom security.
5 BY adding to
6 Article – Courts and Judicial Proceedings
7 Section 1–206
8 Annotated Code of Maryland
9 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
10 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
11 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
12 Article – Courts and Judicial Proceedings
13 1–206.
14 (A) THERE IS A MINIMUM ADEQUATE SECURITY STANDARD FOR
15 COURTROOM SECURITY AT ALL COURTHOUSE FACILITIES IN THE STATE.
16 (B) FOR THE PURPOSES OF THIS SECTION, A COURT SECURITY OFFICER
17 MUST MEET THE QUALIFICATIONS FOR A SPECIAL PEACE POLICE OFFICER AS
18 DEFINED IN § 3–301 OF THE PUBLIC SAFETY ARTICLE.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb0492*

2 HOUSE BILL 492
1 (C) BEGINNING JULY 1, 2027, DURING COURT PROCEEDINGS, ANY ENTITY
2 RESPONSIBLE FOR PROVIDING COURTHOUSE SECURITY SHALL USE BEST EFFORTS
3 TO HAVE PRESENT A MINIMUM OF:
4 (1) ONE COURT SECURITY OFFICER IN EACH COURTROOM FOR ANY
5 CRIMINAL, FAMILY, OR JUVENILE PROCEEDING;
6 (2) TWO COURT SECURITY OFFICERS IN EACH COURTROOM FOR ANY
7 PROCEEDING INVOLVING AN INCARCERATED INDIVIDUAL OR AN INDIVIDUAL WHO
8 MAY BE REMANDED TO CUSTODY AS A RESULT OF THE PROCEEDING; AND
9 (3) ONE ADDITIONAL COURT SECURITY OFFICER FOR EVERY FOUR OR
10 FEWER COURTROOMS ON EACH FLOOR OF A COURTHOUSE.
11 (D) BEGINNING JULY 1, 2029, DURING COURT PROCEEDINGS, ANY ENTITY
12 RESPONSIBLE FOR PROVIDING COURTHOUSE SECURITY SHALL USE BEST EFFORTS
13 TO HAVE PRESENT A MINIMUM OF:
14 (1) ONE COURT SECURITY OFFICER IN EACH COURTROOM FOR ANY
15 TYPE OF PROCEEDING;
16 (2) TWO COURT SECURITY OFFICERS IN EACH COURTROOM FOR ANY
17 PROCEEDING INVOLVING AN INCARCERATED INDIVIDUAL OR ANY INDIVIDUAL WHO
18 MAY BE REMANDED INTO CUSTODY AS A RESULT OF THE PROCEEDING; AND
19 (3) ONE ADDITIONAL COURT SECURITY OFFICER FOR EVERY FOUR OR
20 FEWER COURTROOMS ON EACH FLOOR OF A COURTHOUSE.
21 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
22 October 1, 2026.
Approved:
